  <h1>
   is_bool
  </h1>
  This function returns whether a given variable is a boolean (
  <span>
   true
  </span>
  ior
  <span>
   false
  </span>
  ) or not. In some cases you want to check and see if a variable in
  <span>
   GameMaker
  </span>
  holds a boolean value, and that's when you would use this function.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">is_bool(n);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      n
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm#variable">
        Variable
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The argument to check.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Boolean
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   <b>
    Example:
   </b>
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if is_bool(val)
{
    global.Sound = val;
}
else
{
    global.Sound = true;
}
</code></pre>
  The above code checks the variable "val" to see if it is a real number and if it is it then uses it to set a global variable.
 </body>
